ESRF stands for European Synchrotron Radiation Facility[http://www.esrf.eu].
It is located in Grenoble (France) and produce high quality x-ray beam for scientific research.

----
ESRF has been the first synchrotron of third generation being built in the world.
Financed by almost all European countries, it has produced the first light in 1992.
Since 1994 it welcomes external users coming from all around the world.
The number of users constantly increased since the opening and it has now reached 6000 per year.

With an annual production of about 1500 publications spanning all fields (chemistry, material science, biology ...) it is a center of high-profile research.